post_text:
Please see the below message from the Westampton Recreation Department:

The Westampton Recreation Department is looking for interested candidates to work as caregivers for our Remote Care Program (school-day hours) and After-School Care Program during the 2020-21 school year. This will be a temporary position. Full- and part-time hours available, Monday through Friday, 8am -6pm, while the Westampton School district is teaching remotely. The position could extend longer, depending on how the next phase of in-class teaching happens moving forward from full remote classes.

To apply in person:

Westampton Municipal Building
710 Rancocas Rd
Westampton, NJ 08060

We will accept applications from 9am-3pm on the following days:

Tuesday, 8/25
Wednesday, 8/26
Thursday, 8/27

post_text: Congratulations to even more of our band students representing Westampton in outside Honors Bands. Up first are seventh graders Alex Perkowski, trumpet, Jackson Wright, flute, and Madison Jennings, clarinet. They have been accepted into the West Burlington County Honors Band taking place on April 2nd. Next up are sixth graders Lucas Olsen, trombone and Dalton Kimball, flute. They were recommended and accepted into the All South Jersey Elementary Honors Band for grades 4, 5, & 6 taking place on April 25th. All of them work very hard and Ms. Beekman is so happy to see her students playing their best and showing their Giant Pride through music. Job well done!

post_text: This was a community service project that was organized by Mrs Hammell along with Mrs. Sciarra, the student teacher in Mrs Eckert and Mrs Pancheri’s class. The project incorporated both writing and math curriculum standards that encouraged students to write persuasive letters for their families to donate old t-shirts. The students then used the donations to make 100 dog toys. The shelter arranged for a special visitor to come and accept the donations and teach the students more about the shelter. The students were also given the opportunity to think of names for the puppy awaiting adoption. Sara’s name was chosen and the little guy got the name, Bosco!

post_text: Students in Mrs. Collins’ class have been gathering up the books from Holly Hills families for our Book Drive!! Thank you in for helping to spread the word about our CHOP (Children's Hospital of Philadelphia) Reach Out and Read used book drive. The book drive will run from Monday, January 6th through Friday, January 17th. Any gently used books for children birth to 10 years old will be accepted. Books can be sent in with your student or dropped off at the Holly Hills main office. Please consider taking part in our community service project which is being held to honor Dr. Martin Luther King Jr.'s Day of Service on Monday, 1/20.
